## üõ†Ô∏è Manual Technical Workflow (For Experienced Developers)

### Git Setup
```bash
# Choose appropriate branch type:
git checkout main
git pull origin main

# For copy/content changes:
git checkout -b docs/update-[description]

# For bug fixes:
git checkout -b fix/[description]

# For new features:
git checkout -b feat/[description]

# For maintenance (icons, deps, etc.):
git checkout -b chore/[description]
```

### Make Your Changes
- Edit the relevant files
- Test your changes locally if needed
- Follow project conventions

### Commit and Push
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "docs: update installation instructions"
# or
git commit -m "fix: correct typo in button component"
# or
git commit -m "feat: add new user dashboard section"

git push origin [your-branch-name]
```

